article.headline: Oklahoma St. 91, Grambling St. 60
article.story: STILLWATER, Okla. -- Terrel Harris scored 23 points and James Anderson added 22 to lead Oklahoma State to a 91-60 victory over Grambling State on Sunday. Two runs helped the Cowboys (4-0) pull away from the Tigers. A 17-1 first-half spurt begun by 3-pointer from Harris, Anderson and Nick Sidorakis gave the Cowboys a 38-18 lead before Ariece Perkins ended the run with a field goal for Grambling State. Andrew Priestly narrowed the deficit to 38-26 for the Tigers (0-3), but Anderson responded with a trey to push the lead back to 15 points. With a runner from Donald Qualls at the buzzer, Grambling State trailed 41-28 at intermission. The Tigers opened the second half with another bucket from Qualls, making it 41-30, but Oklahoma State responded and pushed the lead to 57-32 with 13:37 to play. Ibrahim Kpaka led Grambling State with 16 points, Priestly scored 14 and Qualls finished with 11.
